    "en": {
      "title": "13 billion color photos of the ancient universe released",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "In the past 13 billion years ago, NASA has managed to photograph the location of galaxies in the universe and how galaxies were created, and the American President Joe Biden made the photographs public during a press conference held at the White House.",
        "13 billion years ago, this is the first time in history that we have been able to obtain colorful images showing the location of galaxies in the universe and how galaxies formed. Previously, man had not been able to observe the universe backwards through time.",
        "At the press conference, President Joe Biden pointed out that these photos will help astronomers to further expand our knowledge of the universe and uncover the secrets of the universe.",
        "NASA took a picture of the 13 billion-year-old universe with the help of the 'James Webb' space telescope. NASA has introduced that 'James Webb' is a telescope looking into the past. It took 24 years to build this telescope. The telescope was sent into space and stayed in space in 2021.",
        "The telescope, a million miles from Earth, scans the light emitted by stars and galaxies. The telescope tracks light from stars and galaxies back 13.7 billion light-years.",
        "This is possible because it is held and orbited at a great distance from Earth. That's how it happened to photograph how galaxies were located in the universe 13 billion years ago and how galaxies were created. Although NASA took the initiative, the European Space Agency and the Canadian Space Agency have also contributed to the production of the James Webb satellite."
      ],
